# Store PNGs in Git LFS so the repository stays lightweight: the Examples/ proof exports and
# the Documentation/ screenshots. GitHub renders LFS images in the README, and the golden DOT
# exports beside the example PNGs stay plain text on purpose so they remain reviewable.
*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Exception: the app icon is a *build input* — it's compiled into AcaiApp (Assets.xcassets) and
# consumed by Scripts/app_create.sh (sips/iconutil). Keep it a normal git blob so the app still
# builds in a clone without git-lfs (where an LFS file would be a useless text pointer).
Sources/AcaiApp/Resources/Assets.xcassets/**/*.png !filter !diff !merge -text
